1f929.title: Star-Struck
1f929.description: A yellow face with a broad, open smile, showing upper teeth on most platforms, with stars for eyes, as if seeing a beloved celebrity. Color of stars widely varies by platform, though commonly gold or red. May express that someone or something is amazing, fascinating, impressive, or exciting. Star-Struck was approved as part of Unicode 10.0 in 2017 under the name “Grinning Face With Star Eyes” and added to Emoji 5.0 in 2017.

1f92a.title: Zany Face
aliases: Grinning Face With One Large and One Small Eye
1f92a.description: A smiley making a silly face. A yellow face with a big grin and wide, white eyes, one larger than the other and in a wild, cockeyed expression. Many platforms, including Apple, depict its tongue stuck out and head tilted; others feature a full-toothed grin, giving it a more unhinged appearance. Commonly represents such activities as acting goofy, having fun, and partying as well as various senses of slang terms like crazy, usually in a positive manner. May convey a spirit of wackiness more generally. Zany Face was approved as part of Unicode 10.0 in 2017 under the name “Grinning Face With One Large and One Small Eye” and added to Emoji 5.0 in 2017.

1f92d.title: Face With Hand Over Mouth
aliases: Blushing Face With Hand Over Mouth
Smiling Face With Smiling Eyes and Hand Covering Mouth
1f92d.description: A yellow face with a hand covering its mouth. Apple and Facebook feature simple, open eyes, suggesting someone gasping Oh my! in serious surprise, shock, concern, or apology. Other platforms depict a face with smiling eyes and/or blushing cheeks, suggesting coy laughter or embarrassment, as if cheekily saying Oops! May be used to similar effect as 🙊 Speak-No-Evil Monkey. See also 🤐 Zipper-Mouth Face. Joins 🤗 Hugging Face, 🤔 Thinking Face, and 🤫 Shushing Face as one of the few smileys featuring hands. Facebook's design previously featured smiling eyes and mouth. Face With Hand Over Mouth was approved as part of Unicode 10.0 in 2017 under the name “Smiling Face With Smiling Eyes and Hand Covering Mouth” and added to Emoji 5.0 in 2017.

1f92b.title: Shushing Face
aliases: Face With Finger Covering Closed Lips
1f92b.description: A yellow face placing an index finger over pursed lips, as if issuing Shh! or Shush! for silence. Some platforms feature raised eyebrows. Apple’s design suggests the face is tilting back slightly. May convey silence, quiet, secrecy, and discreetness. May also create a sense of buzz and anticipation, e.g., an exclusive sneak peek or news scoop. See also 🤐 Zipper-Mouth Face. Joins 🤗 Hugging Face, 🤔 Thinking Face, and 🤭 Face With Hand Over Mouth as one of the few smileys featuring hands. Shushing Face was approved as part of Unicode 10.0 in 2017 under the name “Face With Finger Covering Closed Lips” and added to Emoji 5.0 in 2017.

1f928.title: Face With Raised Eyebrow
1f928.description: A yellow face with a flat, neutral mouth and furrowed eyebrows, its left raised higher than its right. Conveys a wide variety of sentiments, including suspicion, skepticism, concern, consideration, disbelief, and disapproval. Its expression has notably been likened to the signature look of comedian Stephen Colbert as well as actor/wrestler Dwayne “The Rock” Johnson. Face With Raised Eyebrow was approved as part of Unicode 10.0 in 2017 under the name “Face With One Eyebrow Raised” and added to Emoji 5.0 in 2017.

1f92e.title: Face Vomiting
1f92e.description: A yellow face with scrunched, X-shaped eyes spewing bright-green vomit. May represent physical illness or disgust, more intensely so than 🤢 Nauseated Face. Face Vomiting was approved as part of Unicode 10.0 in 2017 under the name “Face With Open Mouth Vomiting” and added to Emoji 5.0 in 2017.

1f92f.title: Exploding Head
1f92f.description: A yellow face with an open mouth, the top of its head exploding in the shape of a brain-like mushroom cloud. A visual form of the expression mind blown, it may represent such emotions as shock, awe, amazement, and disbelief. Apple’s design features the same expression as its 😦 Frowning Face With Open Mouth. Exploding Head was approved as part of Unicode 10.0 in 2017 under the name “Shocked Face With Exploding Head” and added to Emoji 5.0 in 2017.

1f9d0.title: Face With Monocle
1f9d0.description: A yellow face with furrowed eyebrows wearing a monocle. Usually depicted with a small, intent frown and head slightly upturned, as if in careful inspection. May show that someone is pondering, considering, or questioning something, sometimes with a sense of skeptical or ironic observation or encouraging a closer look at some content. May convey a sense of sophistication or smug intelligence, e.g., smarty-pants. Face With Monocle was approved as part of Unicode 10.0 in 2017 and added to Emoji 5.0 in 2017.

1f92c.title: Face With Symbols on Mouth
aliases: Serious Face With Symbols Covering Mouth
1f92c.description: An angry-red face with a black bar and white grawlixes covering its mouth, indicating it's swearing or being vulgar. Grawlixes are typographical symbols (e.g., @#$%&!) representing swear words or obscenities. Often used to convey an outburst of anger, frustration, or rage. Most platforms feature the same eyes as on their 😠 Angry Face. Face With Symbols on Mouth was approved as part of Unicode 10.0 in 2017 under the name “Serious Face With Symbols Covering Mouth” and added to Emoji 5.0 in 2017.

1f932.title: Palms Up Together
1f932.description: Two hands held out together with open palms facing up, in a slightly cupped manner. May be used to represent an open book in American Sign Language (ASL), or the gesture used by followers of Islam when praying. This gesture also appears similarly to one used to beg for for money. Palms Up Together was approved as part of Unicode 10.0 in 2017 and added to Emoji 5.0 in 2017.

1f931.title: Breast-Feeding
1f931.description: A woman breastfeeding a child. This emoji supports skin tone modifiers, which apply to the mother. The head of the baby is recommended to be hidden to avoid a situation where the skin tone of the baby would only correlate to the skin tone of the mother. Breast-Feeding was approved as part of Unicode 10.0 in 2017 and added to Emoji 5.0 in 2017.

1f993.title: Zebra
1f993.description: A zebra, a horse-like mammal with black-and-white stripes. Variously depicted in full profile on all fours facing left or as a zebra head facing left with a short mane. Not to be confused with 🐎 Horse. Some vendors implement a similar face as their 🐴 Horse Face. Apple, WhatsApp, and Facebook’s designs feature the full animal; Google, Microsoft, and Samsung’s designs feature a head with a short mane and black muzzle. Facebook’s design previously featured only a zebra head. Zebra was approved as part of Unicode 10.0 in 2017 under the name “Zebra Face” and added to Emoji 5.0 in 2017.

1f992.title: Giraffe
1f992.description: A giraffe, the tallest animal on Earth, with spots and a long neck. Generally depicted in yellow or tan in full profile on all fours facing left, with distinctive brown spots and small, horn-like structures. Microsoft and Samsung’s designs feature a giraffe face looking straight ahead. Facebook’s design previously featured only a giraffe face. Giraffe was approved as part of Unicode 10.0 in 2017 under the name “Giraffe Face” and added to Emoji 5.0 in 2017.

1f994.title: Hedgehog
1f994.description: A hedgehog, a small, spiny mammal sometimes kept as a pat. Generally depicted in full profile on all fours facing left, with a round, brown body covered with spines and a light-brown face and underside. Sometimes used to represent a porcupine or echidna. Google and Twitter’s designs show a hedgehog facing forward. Apple and WhatsApp’s design suggest a slight smile. Facebook’s design previously featured a hedgehog on its back, rolled up in a ball. Hedgehog was approved as part of Unicode 10.0 in 2017 and added to Emoji 5.0 in 2017.

1f995.title: Sauropod
1f995.description: A sauropod, a massive, plant-eating dinosaur with a long neck and nail. Depicted as a blue, gray, or green sauropod, as a brachiosaurus, apatosaurus/brontosaurus, or diplodocus. Shown in full profile on all fours facing left. May be used to represent various dinosaurs. See also 🦖 T-Rex. Apple, Google, Samsung, and Facebook’s sauropods resemble a brachiosaurus. Samsung’s sauropod was previously green, Facebook’s only a green head. Sauropod was approved as part of Unicode 10.0 in 2017 and added to Emoji 5.0 in 2017.

1f996.title: T-Rex
1f996.description: A Tyrannosaurus rex, a massive, meat-eating dinosaur with huge jaws, tiny arms, and a long tail. Depicted as a green or brown tyrannosaur standing on its hind lefts facing left, often with a textured back, sharp teeth, and clawed toes. May be used to represent various dinosaurs, including raptors. See also 🦕 Sauropod. Google’s T-Rex resembles a velociraptor. Samsung’s T-Rex was previously red, Facebook’s only a green head with open jaws. T-Rex was approved as part of Unicode 10.0 in 2017 and added to Emoji 5.0 in 2017.

1f997.title: Cricket
1f997.description: A cricket, a hopping insect that makes a chirping sound. Depicted as a brown or green cricket in full profile on its six legs facing left, with long antennae and large, bent back legs. May resemble or be used to represent a grasshopper (including locusts) and other bugs. May also be used to represent metaphorical crickets, or "silence," as of a disapproving or uninterested audience. Not to be confused with 🏏 Cricket Game, the sport. Google's cricket was previously green. Cricket was approved as part of Unicode 10.0 in 2017 and added to Emoji 5.0 in 2017.

1f965.title: Coconut
1f965.description: The hairy shell of a tropical coconut, cracked in a half to show its milky-white meat. Google displays a whole coconut alongside a half-shell. Coconut was approved as part of Unicode 10.0 in 2017 and added to Emoji 5.0 in 2017.

1f966.title: Broccoli
1f966.description: A rich green, tree-like head or floret of broccoli. Broccoli was approved as part of Unicode 10.0 in 2017 and added to Emoji 5.0 in 2017.

1f968.title: Pretzel
1f968.description: The heart-shaped twist of a hard or soft golden-brown pretzel, seasoned with grains of salt. A snack commonly associated with Germany. Pretzel was approved as part of Unicode 10.0 in 2017 and added to Emoji 5.0 in 2017.

1f969.title: Cut of Meat
1f969.description: A cut of uncooked red meat, as a T-bone or rib-eye steak, with the light, white marbling of fat. May be used for sexual slang. Cut of Meat was approved as part of Unicode 10.0 in 2017 and added to Emoji 5.0 in 2017.

1f96a.title: Sandwich
1f96a.description: A sandwich, as eaten at lunch, made with lettuce, tomato, and cheese on slices of white or wheat bread. Apple, Google, and WhatsApp add a deli meat that resembles ham. Sandwich was approved as part of Unicode 10.0 in 2017 and added to Emoji 5.0 in 2017.

1f963.title: Bowl With Spoon
1f963.description: A bowl with a silver spoon inside, as used to eat cereal or soup. Bowl color varies across platforms, as do contents. Android depicts breakfast cereal, WhatsApp tomato soup; Apple’s is empty. Bowl With Spoon was approved as part of Unicode 10.0 in 2017 and added to Emoji 5.0 in 2017.

1f96b.title: Canned Food
1f96b.description: A can or tin of food, depicted as tomatoes or a generic green vegetable. May be also used to represent sauce or soup. Canned Food was approved as part of Unicode 10.0 in 2017 and added to Emoji 5.0 in 2017.

1f95f.title: Dumpling
1f95f.description: A dumpling of dough and filling, as folded and pinched closed for steaming or frying. Associated with cuisines around the world, including China (jiaozi), Japan (gyoza or dango), Poland (pierogi), and Spain and Latin America (empanada). Facebook's design resembles a xiaolongbao, a Chinese soup dumpling. Dumpling was approved as part of Unicode 10.0 in 2017 and added to Emoji 5.0 in 2017.

1f960.title: Fortune Cookie
1f960.description: A golden-brown, crescent-shaped, vanilla-flavored fortune cookie. Usually depicted with a strip of paper—on which a wise saying, lucky numbers, or Chinese vocabulary is written—peaking out of its hollow shell. Given at the end of meals at Chinese restaurants in the West. Fortune Cookie was approved as part of Unicode 10.0 in 2017 and added to Emoji 5.0 in 2017.

1f961.title: Takeout Box
1f961.description: A tall, folded, paper carton, usually white, as used for takeout/takeaway food at Western Chinese restaurants. Most platforms depict chopsticks inside its open lid, labeled with a red, multi-tiered, traditional Chinese building. Also called an oyster pail. Takeout Box was approved as part of Unicode 10.0 in 2017 and added to Emoji 5.0 in 2017.

1f967.title: Pie
1f967.description: A baked dish with a pastry crust, filled with sweet or savory ingredients. Appearance widely varies by platform. Apple depicts a whole pie in a tin, its crimped crust scored to let out steam. Google shows a slice of pumpkin pie as served at Thanksgiving, WhatsApp and Twitter a slice of cherry pie. Pie was approved as part of Unicode 10.0 in 2017 and added to Emoji 5.0 in 2017.

1f964.title: Cup With Straw
1f964.description: A drinking cup with a straw. Depicted on many platforms as a disposable cup with a lid and bendy straw, as used to serve soft drinks at fast-food restaurants. May be used for a range of non-alcoholic beverages, including milkshakes, smoothies, juice, and to-go beverages. Color and design vary by platform. Twitter's design suggests a glass of water, Samsung displays Slightly Smiling Face on a red label. Cup With Straw was approved as part of Unicode 10.0 in 2017 and added to Emoji 5.0 in 2017.

1f962.title: Chopsticks
1f962.description: A pair of equal-length chopsticks, an eating utensil used throughout East Asia. Design and color vary widely by platform, though often red or wood-colored and with tips angled together. Featured in many platforms' Steaming Bowl of Food and Takeout Box. A counterpart to utensils such as Fork and Knife and Spoon. Chopsticks was approved as part of Unicode 10.0 in 2017 and added to Emoji 5.0 in 2017.

1f6f8.title: Flying Saucer
1f6f8.description: A flying saucer, sometimes referred to as an Unidentified Flying Object (UFO). Shown on some platforms with an alien at the controls and/or a beam of light emitting from the base. Flying Saucer was approved as part of Unicode 10.0 in 2017 and added to Emoji 5.0 in 2017.

1f6f7.title: Sled
1f6f7.description: A sled, otherwise known as a toboggan or sledge. Sled was approved as part of Unicode 10.0 in 2017 and added to Emoji 5.0 in 2017.

1f9e5.title: Coat
1f9e5.description: A winter jacket, shown in a variety of colors and styles. Coat was approved as part of Unicode 10.0 in 2017 and added to Emoji 5.0 in 2017.

1f3f4-e0067-e0062-e0065-e006e-e0067-e007.title: Flag: England
1f3f4-e0067-e0062-e0065-e006e-e0067-e007.description: The flag for England, a country in the United Kingdom. May show as the letters gbeng. The Flag: England emoji is a sequence of the 🏴 Waving Black Flag, 󠁧 Tag Latin Small Letter G, 󠁢 Tag Latin Small Letter B, 󠁥 Tag Latin Small Letter E, 󠁮 Tag Latin Small Letter N, 󠁧 Tag Latin Small Letter G and 󠁿 Cancel Tag emojis. These display as a single emoji on supported platforms. Flag: England was added to Emoji 5.0 in 2017.

The Flag: Scotland emoji is a sequence of the 🏴 Waving Black Flag, 󠁧 Tag Latin Small Letter G, 󠁢 Tag Latin Small Letter B, 󠁳 Tag Latin Small Letter S, 󠁣 Tag Latin Small Letter C, 󠁴 Tag Latin Small Letter T and 󠁿 Cancel Tag emojis. 1f3f4-e0067-e0062-e0077-e006c-e0073-e007.title: Flag: Wales
